-- Foxconn says 40 hurt in fight at China plant
-- 
-- Mon Sep 24, 2012 12:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/24/us-honhai-fight-idUSBRE88N04B20120924

 

 TAIPEI  (Reuters) - Taiwan's Foxconn Technology Group said on Monday that 40 people were injured in a fight triggered by a non-work related dispute at its Taiyuan plant in northern China, while a number were arrested. 
 The company said in a statement that a personal dispute between several employees late on Sunday escalated into an incident involving some 2,000 workers, and was brought under control by local police early on Monday. It said it was investigating the incident. (Reporting by  Jonathan Standing ; Editing by  Ken Wills )